  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nCurrently, when storing the link references for a given piece of bytecode, the linked libraries are simply given by name.  However, names can be ambiguous.  Instead, the link references should in some way refer to the actual `Contract` object for the linked library (or something similarly appropriate), both because this removes the ambiguity and because users of DB are going to want to be able to get this information.\r\n\r\nI believe @gnidan has some plan to address this involving something called `ProcessedBytecode`, analogous to `ProcessedSource`, but I'm not familiar with the details; I'm just stating the issue.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.19",
